&lt;h1 id="how-to-do-philosophy"&gt;How to Do Philosophy&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;September 2007&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In high school I decided I was going to study philosophy in college. I had several motives, some more honorable than others. One of the less honorable was to shock people. College was regarded as job training where I grew up, so studying philosophy seemed an impressively impractical thing to do. Sort of like slashing holes in your clothes or putting a safety pin through your ear, which were other forms of impressive impracticality then just coming into fashion.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Is It Worth Being Wise?</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/wisdom/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/wisdom/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/wisdom/"&gt;中文版&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
